Package: cleanroomGov
Title: Clean-Room Governance and Estimand-Reporting Templates
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Andrew", "Mertens", email = "amertens@berkeley.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Structured note-taking and reporting helpers for the staged,
    outcome-blind clean-room workflow: event-process classification aligned
    with ICH E9(R1) intercurrent-event strategies, target-population and
    missing-data declarations, cumulative-incidence coherence checks, and
    cumulative-risk reporting tables. These helpers record and format the
    analytic specification a clean-room review requires; they do not estimate
    any causal quantity and have no dependency on the estimation engine. They
    were split out of the 'cleanTMLE' package so that the estimation package
    carries only estimators, diagnostics, and the enforcing gate.
